EARLY S . AFRICAN SHARE FUTURES FIRMER ON BONDS . 0718 GMT - South African share futures start slightly firmer in quiet trade helped by a stronger bond market . Gold contracts untraded but stronger bullion seen supporting . Dealers say market still shell - shocked after Wednesday ' s fall and nervous ahead of Q1 GDP figure due at 0730 GMT . Market seen picking up during the day but with no major conviction . Cash market seen positive . The all - share contract last at 6 , 372 / 80 from 6 , 365 , the industrial contract is at 7 , 980 / 85 from 7 , 975 and the gold contract is at 825 / 38 from 828 . - - Johannesburg newsroom , + 27 11 482 1003 
